<paragraph id="8BE522713613FFB3F0E5FC9DFECDA58E" blockId="12.[136,1452,236,919]" pageId="12" pageNumber="78">
Etymology. The specific name “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A59F23613FFB3F24AFC9DFDD7A56C" authorityName="Pan &amp; Ren" authorityYear="2018" box="[530,613,860,884]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Meloe" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="78" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scabrus">
<emphasis id="B92EFE633613FFB3F24AFC9DFDD7A56C" box="[530,613,860,884]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="78">scabrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” is a Latin adjective (= scabrous), referring to its large and irregular punctation on head and pronotum.
</paragraph>
